National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan spoke with Republic of Korea National Security Advisor Kim Sung-han to discuss President Biden's upcoming visit to the Republic of Korea. They congratulated Mr. Kim on his appointment and emphasized the importance of the meeting between President Biden and President Yoon in highlighting the strength of the U.S.-ROK Alliance. They condemned the Democratic People's Republic of Korea's ballistic missile launches as a violation of United Nations Security Council resolutions and expressed their commitment to addressing the threats posed by the DPRK and achieving the complete denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. The conversation also touched upon additional details about the President's visit and strengthening cooperation on shared foreign policy priorities.